-- Japan Osaka Gas to buy LNG from Russia's Sakhalin
-- 
-- Fri Feb 9, 2007 1:37am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/09/us-japan-osakagas-lng-idUST1203720070209

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Osaka Gas Co. ( 9532.T ), Japan's second largest natural gas distributor, said on Friday it has agreed to buy liquefied natural gas (LNG) from the Sakhalin-2 project in Russia's far east. 


 Osaka Gas said in a statement it would buy 200,000 tons of LNG from the project every year for 23 years.